Kovi Privacy Policy

Effective: July 8, 2026

Kovi is a face wellness application that guides users through
facial yoga routines, personalized improvement plans, and
skincare habit tracking. This policy explains what data we
handle, why, and how you can control it.

1. Who We Are
Kovi is operated by Kovieloer. Privacy questions can be sent to:
mhernandez1902@hotmail.com

2. Data We Collect

a) Account data — username (5–6 English letters), login account,
optional profile photo, and personal bio. If you use Sign in with
Apple, we receive only Apple's anonymised user identifier token;
we do not receive or store your Apple ID email or credentials.

b) Content you create — posts, comments, and cover images you
choose to publish within the app. All content is stored on your
device and only shared with the community when you explicitly tap
"Publish."

c) Wellness activity data — completed session counts, day streaks,
personal best activity scores, and improvement plan progress.
This data is stored entirely on your device in local JSON files.
It is never transmitted to any server.

d) Purchase receipts — when you subscribe to Kovi Premium or send
a virtual appreciation sticker ("Cheer"), Apple forwards a
transaction receipt for entitlement verification via StoreKit 2.
We do not receive your payment card details.

e) Device metadata — iOS version, device model, and crash logs.
Used solely for app stability improvements.

3. Camera and Face Detection

Kovi uses the front camera in one specific feature: the Face
Analysis screen, which precedes your personalized wellness plan
setup.

What we do:
• Apple's Vision framework (VNDetectFaceRectanglesRequest) detects
  whether a human face is present in the camera frame. This
  confirmation triggers the plan-setup animation sequence.
• All processing happens entirely on your device (on-device
  inference). No camera frames, images, or video are transmitted
  to any server.

What we do NOT do:
• We do not capture, save, or store any face images.
• We do not collect facial landmarks, measurements, geometry, or
  any biometric identifiers.
• We do not perform facial recognition or biometric identification.
• We do not share any face-related data with any third party.

The wellness activity scores displayed after the Face Analysis
screen are general suggestions based on a static dataset defined
in the app. They are NOT computed from your camera feed or any
analysis of your face.

The camera session ends automatically when the Face Analysis screen
closes. Data retention: zero — no face data is retained for any
duration.

4. Photo Library

With your permission, Kovi accesses your photo library to let you:
• Select a profile avatar from your photos.
• Choose a cover image when publishing a post.
• Send a wellness photo in the in-app advisor chat.

Photos are accessed only when you initiate these actions. Selected
images are stored locally on your device. No photos are uploaded
to any server.

5. How We Use Your Data

We use the data above to:
• Operate the Kovi platform and deliver features.
• Verify your Premium subscription entitlements.
• Display your public posts and comments to other members.
• Respond to support requests.
• Improve app stability and performance.
• Comply with applicable law.

We do not sell your personal data. We do not use your photos,
face data, or content to train any AI or machine learning model.

6. AI-Assisted Features

The Kovi Face Care Advisor operates entirely on-device using a
local keyword-matching system implemented in Swift. Responses are
selected from a pre-written wellness tip library based on keywords
in your message. No user input, conversation content, or device
data is transmitted to any server or third-party AI service.

The app does not use OpenAI, Google, Anthropic, or any other
external machine learning service. The face detection feature uses
Apple's own Vision framework, which runs entirely on your device.

7. In-App Purchases and Virtual Items

Kovi Premium is an auto-renewing subscription that delivers new
face wellness routines, personalized daily plans, and expert
content on an ongoing basis.

Virtual appreciation stickers ("Cheer items") are consumable
cosmetic items that allow you to encourage a content creator.
They have no real-world monetary value, cannot be redeemed for
cash, and are not transferable between users.

Payment is charged to your Apple ID at confirmation of purchase.
Manage or cancel subscriptions in iOS Settings → Apple ID →
Subscriptions.

8. Content You Share

Posts and comments you publish publicly are visible to all Kovi
members. You retain ownership of your content. By making content
public you grant Kovi a limited, non-exclusive licence to display
it within the platform. You can delete your public content at any
time from your profile. Deleted content is removed from the app
within 30 days.

9. Third-Party Services

Apple StoreKit 2 — used for in-app purchase processing and
subscription management. Apple's privacy policy applies to
payment processing.

Apple Sign In — if you choose this login method. We receive only
Apple's anonymised user identifier; no Apple account details are
stored by us.

We do not integrate any third-party analytics, advertising, or
tracking SDKs.

10. Data Retention

Account data is retained while your account is active. If you
delete your account in Settings → Delete Account, your personal
data is removed from the app immediately. On-device data
(wellness records, posts, messages) is deleted when you
uninstall the app. We retain no server-side copies of your data.

11. Children

Kovi is not intended for users under 16. We do not knowingly
collect data from children. If you believe a child has created
an account, please contact us and we will remove it promptly.

12. Your Rights

Depending on your location you may have the right to access,
correct, export, or delete your personal data. Because all
personal data is stored on your device, you can exercise most
of these rights directly within the app (Settings → Delete
Account). For additional requests, contact us at
mhernandez1902@hotmail.com. We will respond within 30 days.

13. Security

Sensitive data stored on your device is protected by iOS data
protection (AES-256 encryption). Communications with external
services (legal document loading, StoreKit) use TLS.

14. Updates to This Policy

We may update this policy when our practices change. We will
post the revised policy at the same URL with an updated
effective date. Continued use of Kovi after an update
constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.

